def: A combining form from Greek the nose, as in rhinolith,rhinology.
To convert into a province or provinces. [Obs.] Howell.
A poisonous umbelliferous plant; in England, the Cicuta virosa;in the United States, the Cicuta maculata and the Archemora rigida.See Water hemlock.
To practice psalmody. " The psalmodizing art." J. G. Cooper.
The bright reflection of the moon's light on an expanse ofwater. [Poetic]
A person in a state of somniapathy.
The natural day and night, or space of twenty-four hours.
The Abyssinian or Arabian ibex (Capra Nubiana). It is probablythe wild goat of the Bible.
